Chester v. Jumel et al. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. March 28, 1890.)

Argued before Van Brunt, P. J., and Brady and Daniels, JJ.

E. Winslow Paige, for plaintiff. Everett P. Wheeler, for defendants.

No opinion. Motion denied, with $10 costs. See 4 N. Y. Supp. 955; 5 N. Y. Supp. 809, 819, 822, 823; 7 N. Y. Supp. 949.
